The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Howrah bridge jump after tiff
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Howrah bridge jump after tiff
                            
	Calcutta, Nov. 6: A trader who had a tiff with his wife today jumped off the Howrah bridge in front of her and their two children.         
	Police said Dipak Yadav, 36, a milk trader, was suffering from depression. His body is yet to be recovered.         
	The police said Yadav, who was returning home to Belur, had a quarrel with wife Chandra minutes before plunging into the Ganga around noon. Chandra and the couples two daughters, aged five and seven, started crying and screaming for help. The family was crossing the bridge on foot on their way to Howrah station.        
	Divers have been called in to search for Yadavs body. Fishermen have been asked to help with the search, a police officer said.                                                                                                                                                            
